TeenyLIME - Transiently Shared Tuple Space Middleware 
            for Wireless Sensor Networks

Java Application for the Tunnel Scenario
=====================================================

BUILD INSTRUCTIONS 
------------------ 
0) If not already done, add '$TOSROOT/support/sdk/java/tinyos.jar' 
to your classpath:

$ export CLASSPATH=$CLASSPATH:$TOSROOT/support/sdk/java/tinyos.jar

1) Go to '$TLROOT/apps/tunnel/java/' directory and
build the java application:

$ cd $TLROOT/apps/tunnel/java
$ ant clean && ant

USAGE INSTRUCTIONS
------------------
1) Go to the '$TLROOT/apps/tunnel/java/' directory (or the directory
where the tl.jar file is located) and launch the following command 
with the parameters related to the interface you want to use (console|gui):

$ java -cp tl.jar tl.apps.tunnel.Launcher -comm <source> 
                                         -interface <console|gui>
								 
If no parameter is provided, the command is equal to the following:

$ java -cp tl.jar tl.apps.tunnel.Launcher -comm sf@localhost:9001 
				                           				  -interface gui
